meaning:
'grow dark, be darkened, be black, be enveloped in mist, grow blind (eyes), be obscured (face)'; note that ṣalama ጸለማ (Y) 'hear, cup the ear in order to hear better' is a misprint for ṣalawa ጸለወ.
'aṣlama 'darken, cause to be black, cast darkness, make blind';
ṣalum 'dark, obscured, blinded';
ṣallim (fem. ṣalləm) 'black, dark, gloomy';
ṣalləme (Lt) 'darkness, obscurity';
ṣalmat 'darkness, darkening, eclipse';
(beta ṣalmat 'prison');
(mawə)ṣala ṣalmat 'the days of the month after the 15th', lit. 'the days of the decrease of the light of the moon)';
maṣlam 'dark place, dark, obscure';
denominative from 'ṣalmat 'darkness'; also Tna. ṣälmatä 'be dark', Te. ṣälmata. See ṣalma, above.

'be dark, grow dark';
'aṣalmata 'darken, obscure';
ṣalmut 'darkened, surrounded by darkness, black, clouded over';
ṣalmutawi (Gr.483) 'dark, obscure';
denominative from 'ṣalmat 'darkness'; also Tna. ṣälmatä 'be dark', Te. ṣälmata. See ṣalma, above.

'bake bread';
maṣallat 'unleavened bread';
(ba'əla maṣallat 'feast of Passover'; see Mauro da Leonessa 306);

'listen, incline (the ear), cup the ear in order to hear better';
'aṣlawa (Lt), causative; also 'listen';
ṣalawi (KG), act. part. of ṣalawa;
ṣaləw 'inclined (ear), attentive';
ṣaləwa labb 'inconsistent, not constant' (from the original meaning 'incline', that is, 'not be steady');

'broil, roast';
ṣalawi (K*), act. participle;
maṣlaw, same;

'pray, make a vow, supplicate, plead, intercede';
taṣallaya, passive;
ṣallāyi, act. part. of ṣallaya;
ṣalluy 'blessed (through prayer), consecrated';
ṣalot 'prayer, vow, intercession';
(māya ṣalot 'holy water');
maṣallay 'who prays';
maṣlay 'place of prayer, chapel, oratory';

'be thirsty, thirst';
'aṣma 'make thirsty, cause thirst';
ṣamu 'thirsty, parched (ground)';
ṣamw 'thirst';
maṣma 'that which makes thirsty';
maṣmā 'parched place, arid place';

'fade away, wither, decay, faint, languish, become sluggish, pine away, be flabby, be gloomy, grow melancholy, dry up, be perplexed';
'aṣamḥaya, causative;
taṣamḥaya, same meanings as ṣamḥaya; also 'exhibit a dry appearance', that is, 'put on a sour look';

same meanings as ṣamḥaya, above;
'aṣamḥayaya, 'aṣməḥayaya, 'aṣmähayaya, 'aṣamähayaya, causative;
taṣamḥayaya, taṣamähayaya, (T) taṣamḥayaya, same meanings as ṣamḥaya.

